"use strict";(self["webpackChunkTourDeFantasy"]=self["webpackChunkTourDeFantasy"]||[]).push([[594],{5491:function(e,a,t){t.r(a),t.d(a,{default:function(){return p}});var o=t(6768);const s={class:"about"},r=(0,o.Fv)('<h1 class="mt-4" data-v-223e3e23>Rules</h1><div class="container" data-v-223e3e23><p data-v-223e3e23> TourDeFantasy is the ultimate fantasy sports game that brings the exhilarating world of professional cycling to life. In this game, you become the manager of a team of elite cyclists, competing in the most prestigious races around the globe. Your objective is to strategically draft, manage, and lead your team to victory by earning points based on their real-world performances. From the iconic climbs of the Tour de France to the sprints of Milan-San Remo, experience the thrill and strategy of pro cycling in a whole new way.</p><p data-v-223e3e23> Get ready to ride, strategize, and dominate the leaderboard with TourDeFantasy!</p><div class="accordion" id="accordionExample" data-v-223e3e23><div class="accordion-item" data-v-223e3e23><h2 class="accordion-header" data-v-223e3e23><button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseOne" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="collapseOne" data-v-223e3e23><strong data-v-223e3e23>How to get started</strong></button></h2><div id="collapseOne" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample" data-v-223e3e23><div class="accordion-body" data-v-223e3e23><p data-v-223e3e23><strong data-v-223e3e23> 1. Sign Up</strong></p><p data-v-223e3e23>Visit the TourDeFantasy website and create your account. You can sign up by connecting through your Strava account for quick access.</p><p data-v-223e3e23><strong data-v-223e3e23> 2. Join or Create a League </strong></p><p data-v-223e3e23> Create or join a private league with your friends, family, or colleagues for a more personalized and competitive experience. Join an existing league using the league code.</p><p data-v-223e3e23><strong data-v-223e3e23> 3. Choose a Team Name</strong></p><p data-v-223e3e23> Give your team a unique and exciting name that reflects your style and strategy.</p><p data-v-223e3e23><strong data-v-223e3e23> 4. Set Your Draft List</strong></p><p data-v-223e3e23> Before the race begins, each player will need to set a draft list of cyclists. Here&#39;s how to do it: </p><p data-v-223e3e23> Research Riders: Browse through the list of available professional cyclists. Check out their stats, recent performances, and specialties (e.g., sprinter, climber, time-trialist).</p><p data-v-223e3e23> Prioritize Your Picks: Rank your preferred riders in order of priority on the Draft page. This list will guide the draft selection process, so think strategically about who you want on your team.</p></div></div></div><div class="accordion-item" data-v-223e3e23><h2 class="accordion-header" data-v-223e3e23><button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseTwo" data-v-223e3e23><strong data-v-223e3e23>What does each roster look like?</strong></button></h2><div id="collapseTwo" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample" data-v-223e3e23><div class="accordion-body" data-v-223e3e23><p data-v-223e3e23>Each team manager will have a team of eight riders and four bench/alternate riders. Team managers are able to choose as riders of any speciality.</p></div></div></div><div class="accordion-item" data-v-223e3e23><h2 class="accordion-header" data-v-223e3e23><button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseThree" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseThree" data-v-223e3e23><strong data-v-223e3e23>How does the draft work?</strong></button></h2><div id="collapseThree" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample" data-v-223e3e23><div class="accordion-body" data-v-223e3e23><p data-v-223e3e23> Draft order will be determined randomly before the draft begins. This order will dictate the sequence in which players pick their cyclists. </p><p data-v-223e3e23>When the draft starts, the system will automatically pick cyclists for each team based on the draft order and each player&#39;s prioritized list. To ensure fairness, the system follows a snake format. If you pick last in the first round, youâ€™ll pick first in the second round, and so on.</p></div></div></div><div class="accordion-item" data-v-223e3e23><h2 class="accordion-header" data-v-223e3e23><button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseFour" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFour" data-v-223e3e23><strong data-v-223e3e23>When can you change your line up?</strong></button></h2><div id="collapseFour" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample" data-v-223e3e23><div class="accordion-body" data-v-223e3e23><p data-v-223e3e23>Before each stage in the race, team managers will have the chance to switch out their eight riders with alternates along with trade for new riders. Each team&#39;s lineup will be locked in at the beginning of the stage. If no lineup changes are made, the previous lineup will be used to race. You cannot change your lineup during the stage.</p></div></div></div><div class="accordion-item" data-v-223e3e23><h2 class="accordion-header" data-v-223e3e23><button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseFive" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseFive" data-v-223e3e23><strong data-v-223e3e23>How does trading work?</strong></button></h2><div id="collapseFive" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample" data-v-223e3e23><div class="accordion-body" data-v-223e3e23><p data-v-223e3e23>Besides changing your roster, team managers will also have <strong data-v-223e3e23>one</strong> opportunity between each stage to trade riders that weren&#39;t picked up by anyone in their league. If multiple claims are filed, the manager with the highest trade priority gets the player. If only one claim is filed, the manager automatically gets the player.</p><p data-v-223e3e23>Trade priority is based on the reverse order you drafted in (So the #1 pick has #5priority, the #5 pick has #1 priority). Once you successfully traded a racer, you immediately go to the bottom of the list.</p><p data-v-223e3e23>If multiple claims are filed, the manager(s) that don&#39;t have the highest trade priority don&#39;t get the player, along with lose their chance of the day to trade. So, pick wisely on who to trade!</p><p data-v-223e3e23>Trading opens at 1 pm CST and closes at 8 pm CST of the day before the stage.</p></div></div></div><div class="accordion-item" data-v-223e3e23><h2 class="accordion-header" data-v-223e3e23><button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#collapseSix" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="collapseSix" data-v-223e3e23><strong data-v-223e3e23>How to earn points?</strong></button></h2><div id="collapseSix" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordionExample" data-v-223e3e23><div class="accordion-body" data-v-223e3e23><p data-v-223e3e23>This For each stage, the top 15 riders get 100, 70, 50, 40, 32, 26, 22, 18, 14, 10, 8, 6, 4, 2, 1 points respectively. For sprinting, riders get the same points as the pcs pnt system of &quot;points at finish&quot;. For KOM/climbing, riders get the same points as pcs system times 5.</p><p data-v-223e3e23>Team managers can receiver bonus for earning multiple jerseys in one day. If you have 2 jerseys on your team, you earn a bonus 20 points. If you have 3 jerseys on your team, you earn a bonus 30 points. If you have all jerseys on your team, you earn a bonus 50 points.</p><p data-v-223e3e23>At the end of the race, there are several bonuses you can receive. The top 15 riders in the general classification get a bonus of 100, 70, 50, 40, 32, 26, 22, 18, 14, 10, 8, 6, 4, 2, 1 points respectively. The top 3 youth riders 30, 20, 10 points respectively. The GC and Youth are only applicable to the active riders on your roster not your bench riders.</p></div></div></div></div></div>',2),i=[r];function n(e,a){return(0,o.uX)(),(0,o.CE)("div",s,i)}var d=t(1241);const c={},l=(0,d.A)(c,[["render",n],["__scopeId","data-v-223e3e23"]]);var p=l}}]);
